00:15:02.177 --> 00:15:04.510
So a lot of people in the
leading business talks-- and I

00:15:04.510 --> 00:15:07.360
mean the most popular talks of
all time-- were using a story.

00:15:07.360 --> 00:15:09.220
They were using a
story to be humorous.

00:15:09.220 --> 00:15:11.260
Thing is, if you tell a
story and the funny bit

00:15:11.260 --> 00:15:13.690
is moved to the end
quite consciously

00:15:13.690 --> 00:15:16.314
to delay the element of surprise
the same way we would show--

00:15:16.314 --> 00:15:17.980
and we mentioned with
the images later--

00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:21.340
delay that surprise twist
until the end, if they laugh,

00:15:21.340 --> 00:15:22.110
fantastic.

00:15:22.110 --> 00:15:23.950
It gives a maximum
chance of laughing.

00:15:23.950 --> 00:15:26.420
And if they don't,
nothing happens.

00:15:26.420 --> 00:15:28.714
They don't know you were
trying to be funny in any way.

00:15:28.714 --> 00:15:30.130
Do you ever have
that moment where

00:15:30.130 --> 00:15:31.390
your boss calls
you into an office,

00:15:31.390 --> 00:15:32.350
and they're like, oh, sit down.

00:15:32.350 --> 00:15:33.600
I've got a great joke for you.

00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:35.980
And you're like, oh, god,
get me out of here now.

00:15:35.980 --> 00:15:37.750
They've already
telegraphed the intention

00:15:37.750 --> 00:15:39.940
of what they're about to do.

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:42.494
So you already have a
massive chance of failure.

00:15:42.494 --> 00:15:44.410
And the other thing on
this that is pretty key

00:15:44.410 --> 00:15:46.210
is, if you want to
create memorable content

00:15:46.210 --> 00:15:47.440
or information and
you want people

00:15:47.440 --> 00:15:48.856
to be able to tell
it back to you,

00:15:48.856 --> 00:15:51.070
they have to be able to
visualize it actually

00:15:51.070 --> 00:15:52.040
happening.

00:15:52.040 --> 00:15:54.970
So nobody cares
about your story.

00:15:54.970 --> 00:15:57.640
They care about themselves
within your story.

00:15:57.640 --> 00:16:00.456
So if they can't visualize
themselves within your story,

00:16:00.456 --> 00:16:02.830
or you're telling them even
a client's story in your case

00:16:02.830 --> 00:16:04.670
when you're pitching
in a business context,

00:16:04.670 --> 00:16:07.810
if you don't put features on
that story that their mind can

00:16:07.810 --> 00:16:10.390
actually visualize,
they cannot remember it.

00:16:10.390 --> 00:16:12.854
They 100% can't remember
facts and figures.

00:16:12.854 --> 00:16:14.770
So you never want to
lead any pitch or meeting

00:16:14.770 --> 00:16:16.686
with facts or figures,
because your brain just

00:16:16.686 --> 00:16:17.590
can't remember them--

00:16:17.590 --> 00:16:19.390
very, very difficult.
They're normally the icing

00:16:19.390 --> 00:16:20.667
on the cake and not the lead.

00:16:20.667 --> 00:16:22.750
And a lot of people make
that mistake in pitching.

00:16:22.750 --> 00:16:25.000
But the world's best speakers
will always have a story.

00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:26.620
They're always going to have
that funny bit at the end

00:16:26.620 --> 00:16:28.450
to maximize the chance
of something being funny,

00:16:28.450 --> 00:16:29.825
and they're going
to have details

00:16:29.825 --> 00:16:32.710
into it that you can latch on
to or see yourself with it.

